{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Disability awareness at all levels of national curriculum to prevent bullying",
        "additional_details": "There have been serious cases of bullying for disabilities such as autism, including where children have been hurt or have suffered serious mental health problems as a result. These children are our future - we have to teach children it\u2019s wrong to bully for being different and make them understand it, and the best place is a school environment. Make it a compulsory lesson for all age groups.",
        "background": "Children have a lack of understanding around disabilities, I think this is why some children are bullied for having a disability. Make it compulsory for children to be taught about it and why people may have it. This will help children understand and also help stop children feeling isolated.",
